biography.text:
Five-time GRAMMY® Award-nominated artist and co-founder of Axwell Λ Ingrosso and Swedish House Mafia, Axwell's journey began in Lund, Sweden. In the early 2000s, he gained recognition as a sought-after remixer and co-writer. In 2008, he joined forces with Steve Angello and Sebastian Ingrosso to form Swedish House Mafia, earning back-to-back GRAMMY® nominations for "Best Dance Recording" with hits like "Save the World" (2012) and "Don't You Worry Child" (2013). They sold out iconic venues and delivered historic performances at Coachella and Ultra Music Festival.

Axwell Λ Ingrosso also rose to prominence, releasing their debut album "More Than You Know" in 2017, featuring the gold-certified title track. They headlined Tomorrowland four times. While Swedish House Mafia made a comeback in 2021 with "Paradise Again," reaching #1 on Billboard's Dance/Electronic Albums and UK Dance Albums charts. They embarked on the extensive Paradise Again World Tour, spanning 29 cities in 11 countries on two continents for five months.

Axwell has been a fixture on DJ Mag's "Top 100 DJs" list, earning four DJ Awards and three GRAMMY® Award nominations, including "Best Remixed Recording, Non-Classical" for remixes of songs by Temper Trap and Ivan Gough & Feenixpawl, and a nomination for "Best Rap/Sung Collaboration" for co-producing Flo Rida's "Wild Ones." Axwell continues to push boundaries, with more exciting projects slated for 2023 and beyond.
